<i> ["The Ballad Of</i>
     <i> Gilligan's Isle"]</i>

00:03.537 --> 00:05.504
¶ Just sit right back
    and you'll hear a tale ¶

00:05.573 --> 00:07.973
¶ A tale of a fateful trip ¶

00:08.042 --> 00:09.975
¶ That started
    from this tropic port ¶

00:10.043 --> 00:12.310
¶ Aboard this tiny ship ¶

00:12.379 --> 00:14.846
¶ The mate was
     a mighty sailin' man ¶

00:14.915 --> 00:17.215
¶ The Skipper brave and sure ¶

00:17.284 --> 00:19.451
¶ Five passengers
      set sail that day ¶

00:19.519 --> 00:21.720
¶ For a three hour tour ¶

00:21.789 --> 00:24.556
¶ A three hour tour ¶

00:24.625 --> 00:26.658
[thunder rumbling]

00:26.727 --> 00:28.860
¶ The weather started
     getting rough ¶

00:28.929 --> 00:31.230
¶ The tiny ship was tossed ¶

00:31.298 --> 00:33.832
¶ If not for the courage
    of the fearless crew ¶

00:33.901 --> 00:35.967
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

00:36.036 --> 00:38.303
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

00:38.372 --> 00:40.171
¶ The ship set ground
     on the shore ¶

00:40.240 --> 00:42.974
¶ Of this uncharted
      desert isle ¶

00:43.043 --> 00:45.376
¶ With Gilligan ¶

00:45.445 --> 00:47.779
¶ The Skipper too ¶

00:47.848 --> 00:49.714
¶ The millionaire ¶

00:49.783 --> 00:52.150
¶ And his wife ¶

00:52.219 --> 00:54.886
¶ The movie star ¶

00:54.955 --> 00:56.988
¶ And the rest ¶

00:57.057 --> 01:01.126
¶ Are here on Gilligan's Isle ¶

